Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.85,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(588.5,15)}At the Ruins of the King's Tomb,\Nlocated in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.31,0:00:09.35,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,To the eighteen of you \Nwho passed the first test...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.69,0:00:13.20,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\blur0.2\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}Second Test Proctor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.69,0:00:13.20,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs22\blur0.2\pos(320,265)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}Sense, First-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.21,0:00:13.19,DefaultTop,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,First, congratulations on making it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.01,0:00:21.97,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I hear people speculate all kinds of things \Nabout my tests based on past results.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:27.61,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there are some of you \Nwho have heard such rumors,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.61,0:00:30.08,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,but you needn't prepare \Nyourselves for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.97,0:00:33.20,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,The test is very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.77,0:00:38.29,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who wishes to become a first-class \Nmage should be able to pass it with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.92,0:00:44.05,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, allow me to explain \Nthe details of the second test.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:00:58.03,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.03,0:01:02.66,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.66,0:01:08.29,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.58,0:01:13.63,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:17.01,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:21.60,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.60,0:01:28.35,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.28,0:01:39.49,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.49,0:01:43.70,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:48.08,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:53.09,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.09,0:01:58.47,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:02.51,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:06.93,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.93,0:02:11.77,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:17.99,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(380,269)}Episode 23: Conquering the Labyrinth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.05,0:02:21.85,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,For the second test, \Nyou will be raiding a dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.23,0:02:26.11,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You will raid the Ruins of the King's Tomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.69,0:02:33.88,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one condition for passing: \Nyou must reach the deepest floor of the tomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.29,0:02:39.62,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I am a pacifist. I dislike fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.62,0:02:43.52,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, everyone who reaches \Nthe bottom will pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.77,0:02:44.61,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.65,0:02:50.26,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,Many adventurers have failed to return \Nfrom this unexplored dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:53.16,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to fail \Nall the test-takers again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:54.51,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.71,0:02:59.41,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You are attempting to reach \Nthe pinnacle of magehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:03.63,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,First-class mages make \Nthe impossible possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.26,0:03:09.01,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You must forge ahead, regardless of whether \Nor not anyone's been there before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.40,0:03:15.20,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,How should we prove we've reached the bottom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:18.00,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Should we return with treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.45,0:03:20.48,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You won't need to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:23.64,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I will descend to the bottom \Nof the dungeon with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.08,0:03:27.05,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, I will not be \Nassisting the test-takers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:32.23,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Also, each of you will receive \None of these bottles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.12,0:03:39.13,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,It's an escape golem developed \Nby the first-class mage Lernen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.26,0:03:42.80,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,When the bottle is shattered,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:45.51,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,the golem will manifest \Nand carry you out of the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.31,0:03:49.23,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,They're still prototypes, \Nbut they're safe enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.80,0:03:52.21,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Using your bottle means you fail the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:56.54,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,but I urge you to do so if you become unable \Nto continue due to injuries or otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.01,0:04:00.65,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of allowing mages \Nwith promising futures to die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:06.48,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the bottles will shatter \Nautomatically at dawn tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.45,0:04:10.01,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,That is the time limit of the second test.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:14.43,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let the test begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.95,0:04:38.21,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,There are multiple entrances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:41.50,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This seems to be a dungeon \Nof the Unified Dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.87,0:04:45.68,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Dungeons of that era have multiple entrances,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:48.51,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,but they all lead to the deepest level.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.51,0:04:50.72,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Examining the entrances should allow us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.76,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,to determine the internal \Nstructure of the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.41,0:04:56.27,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The group should split up and—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.27,0:04:59.02,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you acting like \Nwe're working together?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.58,0:05:08.02,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason for us to fight this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.02,0:05:11.29,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's better for all of us to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.55,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,I can't agree to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.57,0:05:20.04,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike in the first test, our companions' \Nsurvival isn't a condition for passing the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:23.54,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,We're not obligated to help each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:27.55,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,and we even risk becoming someone's \Nsacrificial pawn if the need arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:32.04,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,You in particular seem \Nknowledgeable about dungeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.45,0:05:35.17,Default,TON,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:52.16,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,We're all carrying baggage from the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:55.82,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, I can't work \Nwith anyone I don't know well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.13,0:06:00.26,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.85,0:06:04.40,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.04,0:06:13.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Those fools. Why don't they realize \Nworking together is better?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.38,0:06:15.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.54,0:06:18.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure, Ms. Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:22.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no chance of everyone \Nworking together anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.43,0:06:29.94,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:33.92,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I shall accompany your group.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:38.95,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You seem like you'll have the \Nsafest time reaching the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.13,0:06:41.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better not interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:45.90,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I shall neither interfere nor assist you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:56.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the safest route.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.55,0:07:01.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll proceed with caution \Nwhile mapping the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:17.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The floor there is trapped. Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:26.58,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You always know so much about dungeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.26,0:07:30.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't always.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:33.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was Himmel who loved dungeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:38.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We entered so many of them \Nto hunt down monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:42.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, he loved dungeons?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.06,0:07:45.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's exactly what it sounds like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.45,0:07:47.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He said they excited him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.15,0:07:50.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:56.71,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,These stairs lead to the next floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.60,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then we chose the wrong route.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:04.68,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head back to the last branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.68,0:08:06.06,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.31,0:08:11.90,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why? We're looking for the monster \Nat the bottom of the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:15.22,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,When will you learn, Eisen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.46,0:08:21.65,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,In a dungeon, one must explore the entire \Nfloor before proceeding to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.65,0:08:23.62,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Every adventurer knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:25.30,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:29.24,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'm being foolish, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.41,0:08:35.39,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it best to be able to have fun \Nwhile helping people?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.82,0:08:38.30,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It won't always be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:41.08,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,As we travel, the dungeons will \Nbecome more life-threatening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:42.51,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:45.05,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to enjoy it until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.75,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have fun adventuring, raiding dungeons,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:51.74,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,defeating monsters, finding treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.13,0:08:54.75,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,and before I know it, \NI'll have saved the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.59,0:08:58.49,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of adventure I want to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.09,0:09:01.18,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:06.52,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,There might be a rare grimoire \Ndown the path left untraveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.98,0:09:09.43,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Let's hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:10.53,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:14.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It really doesn't make sense, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.05,0:09:30.03,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Kanne, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.45,0:09:46.20,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, only the five of us stayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.93,0:09:50.49,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We could've beaten the dungeon easily
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.49,0:09:53.48,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,if we'd all worked together \Nand assigned roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:58.23,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We had enough skilled mages to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.80,0:10:02.87,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, not everyone is as pragmatic as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.47,0:10:07.20,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It's like what you said \Ntoward the end of the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:12.74,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It must not have sat right with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.33,0:10:17.33,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it this way: \Nonly the smartest have remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.95,0:10:20.11,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.11,0:10:24.77,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,there aren't any idiots here to hold us back \Nby falling for simple traps like mimics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.36,0:10:27.26,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that good enough, Denken?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.92,0:10:31.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt anyone that foolish would \Nbe taking this test to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:34.17,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:45.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This mana...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:48.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a grimoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:52.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you saw the results \Nof that Mikheit spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.93,0:10:55.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.43,0:11:01.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, that spell is only 99% accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.31,0:11:03.43,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,And what if it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:11.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Historical discoveries have been made by \Ngreat mages who recognized that remaining 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.58,0:11:18.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:22.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a valuable grimoire inside here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:27.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what my experience \Nas a mage is telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.39,0:11:36.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark and scary in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.29,0:11:39.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark! I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:42.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark and scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:59.48,DefaultItalics,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I chose the wrong people to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:11.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't step on the floor in the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:13.83,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The ceiling will come crashing down on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.02,0:12:19.91,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that person-shaped stain there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.60,0:12:23.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Brutal. It doesn't even leave bones behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.07,0:12:46.36,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Gargoyles!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.69,0:13:47.01,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, someone got trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:47.97,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:50.22,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,She's on the other side of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.71,0:13:53.32,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.31,0:14:01.81,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.35,0:14:03.56,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Then we have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:05.31,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Break your bottle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:23.71,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:26.35,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We're already down another test-taker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.94,0:14:32.84,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Letting your guard down for a moment \Nhere could cost you your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.46,0:14:37.21,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,So these are the Ruins of the King's Tomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.81,0:14:50.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Fern. Can I make a suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.17,0:14:54.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop pulling. You're going to rip me in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.93,0:14:55.78,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.38,0:15:01.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,To save someone from a mimic, \Nyou should push in instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.14,0:15:04.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It makes the mimic choke and stop biting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.76,0:15:07.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a dog or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:13.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.12,0:15:15.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.95,0:15:19.02,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get out of those \Nwhen you were by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:22.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,By blowing them up from the inside \Nwith offensive magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.03,0:15:26.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't like to do it \Nsince it makes my hair frizz up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:28.02,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.55,0:15:30.75,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I have ringlets now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.40,0:15:35.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you'd sometimes \Nhave a different hairstyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.84,0:15:36.84,Flashback,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.85,0:15:42.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pull ourselves together and keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.73,0:15:52.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Gargoyles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.61,0:15:54.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll defeat them before they start moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.44,0:16:01.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We've been seeing these \Nmedals all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently some dilettante collects them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.54,0:16:12.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This looks like the main route. \NLet's turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.65,0:16:13.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:19.94,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We're progressing more \Nsmoothly than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:24.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It does seem a bit odd \Nfor an unexplored dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.45,0:16:27.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by its construction, \Nwe should be nearing the bottom, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.46,0:16:30.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, don't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:34.95,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a break in the \Nnext burial chamber we find.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.02,0:16:40.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We've acquired some pretty nice stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:42.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It just looks like junk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.40,0:16:44.85,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.20,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.20,0:16:51.45,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:54.89,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why do those things make her happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.63,0:16:58.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's rubbing it on her cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.05,0:17:03.04,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one I don't understand, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:08.58,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen a mage \Nas skilled as you at your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.15,0:17:11.54,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You must have trained rather hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:15.68,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,And yet I sense no passion \Nor determination in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:17.08,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,You're a strange girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.93,0:17:26.43,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I became a proper mage \Nto repay a debt to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.68,0:17:32.44,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That was my life's goal at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:35.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I devoted all my effort to achieving it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.18,0:17:38.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,without considering anything \Nthat would come after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.87,0:17:46.94,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I must've used up all my passion \Nand determination then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.45,0:17:52.60,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Then why do you continue \Nsearching for magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.79,0:17:58.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren seems to be \Nhaving fun, doesn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:17:59.73,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.03,0:18:03.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The first time I entered a dungeon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.78,0:18:10.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren joyfully smiled \Nwhile collecting magic junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:17.78,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It made me smile, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:26.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I think I continue searching for magic \Nbecause I like seeing her happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.90,0:18:31.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.93,0:18:40.55,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I was right \Nto follow you after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.12,0:18:46.06,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you can enjoy \Neven this brutal dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.29,0:19:12.02,Default,SCHARF,0000,0000,0000,,The atmosphere has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.94,0:19:15.45,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we're near the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.22,0:19:19.28,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Wirbel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:21.81,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What? Can't walk any—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.81,0:19:23.52,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm restrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:26.38,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,There are three mages concealing their mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.38,0:19:27.89,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.89,0:19:29.02,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.55,0:19:35.32,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Scharf, block their vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:37.94,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,The spell cast on Ehre is Sorganeil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:38.99,Default,SCHARF,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.49,0:19:58.54,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder the Ruins of the King's Tomb \Nhave never been conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.07,0:20:04.11,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting to encounter these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.89,0:20:07.31,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Scharf, you're on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:09.56,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Ehre, you're on Scharf.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.85,0:20:11.85,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll take on Ehre.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.54,0:20:14.95,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:58.97,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a replica made using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.71,0:21:02.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It must be the work of demons or monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.45,0:21:08.76,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,But I've never seen such a perfect copy \Nof another person before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:12.27,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Its mana and skills were \Nthe same as yours, Laufen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.17,0:21:14.96,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,So was its behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.96,0:21:18.37,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible even our memories were used.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:21.67,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.40,0:21:27.59,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The one saving grace is that it's \Ninstantly recognizable as a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:31.90,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, there's no danger \Nof us attacking each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.34,0:21:38.03,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,If whoever cast this spell can control \Nmultiple copies simultaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.03,0:21:40.55,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,they must be terrifyingly powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:47.19,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we were right to team up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.73,0:21:53.52,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It gives us more options \Nfor dealing with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.65,0:22:22.06,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, can we deal with that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.95,0:22:32.77,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The one thing I can say \Nis that if this weren't a test,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.77,0:22:35.80,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I would've shattered my bottle \Na long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.01,0:22:53.14,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:56.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:23:01.65,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:04.07,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:07.07,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.65,0:23:13.70,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.70,0:23:17.50,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:20.37,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:25.05,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:31.30,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.30,0:23:37.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.06,0:23:43.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:48.94,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:52.99,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.99,0:23:57.62,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:24:00.62,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:03.38,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.38,0:24:06.42,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:12.47,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:19.39,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:23.77,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, what are we going to do about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.85,0:24:22.19,DefaultOverlap,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Smells nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.30,0:24:23.04,DefaultTop,EDEL,0000,0000,0000,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.32,0:24:24.12,DefaultOverlapTop,ÜBEL/ID,0000,0000,0000,,If we're evenly matched,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:25.00,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,That's not funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:26.26,DefaultTop,ÜBEL/ID,0000,0000,0000,,then who wins will come down to luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:26.40,DefaultOverlap,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please look into my eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.78,0:24:27.67,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.29,0:24:28.10,DefaultTop,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,How much time do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.52,0:24:29.98,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 24\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NPerfect Replicas
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.10,0:24:30.03,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,They're perfect replicas.